Movie: Love Has Won: The Cult of Mother God
Review: I didn’t understand a word they said. Did they actually say anything?
This is literally a perfect movie… but maybe don’t watch this while on your period.
Could have lived without this one.
I love the way Christopher Nolan films scratch my brain.
I watched this because I love Jacob Wysocki. I tried to like it..but they were all terrible people. Kudos to them being early on the “told through the computer screen” thing though.

This was one of the first horror movies/series I had ever seen. I remember forcing my sister to watch it with me during the summer, early in the morning when the sun was out so I wouldn’t be so scared. This holds up really well. I was really excited to see it on Hulu, even though this is one of those I have on DVD and will never get rid of.
I’m already starting to memorize the Diva Spell. I yearned for this my entire childhood but summer camp is for the rich kids.
Note to self/PSA, I know it seems obvious not to be eating during THAT scene, but specifically, don’t eat Spaghetti or anything red. 🤢
